last stop.tips: Prioritize a good sniper as gem carrier in middle. In bushes you can run an anti agro, assassin, or brawler good at scouting.

triple dribble.tips: Be wary of late pick throwers since they're very strong here. Utilize good hypercharges and tanks.

bridge too far.tips: Heist rework less punishing with DPS brawlers. Still opt for 2 DPS brawlers and a "clean-up" brawler that will defend or win lanes. Long range or abilities to go on water will win lanes easily.

layer cake.tips: Pressure wins games. You want tanks and brawlers good at wall peaking rather than snipers since there are too many walls.

shooting star.tips: Grab as many good snipers as possible. Get a good thrower or wall peak for middle then run snipers in lane.

ring of fire.tips: For a middle brawler save them for later in the draft since there are plenty to choose from and they're all susceptible to being countered by each other. A basic comp has a mid, brawler to invade enemy grass, and a third to help the other two.

backyard bowl.tips: Use `/event` command to see more info about melodie challenge. This is temporarily set to melodie challenge

belles rock.tips: Don't go too many snipers. If they miss too often they get pushed back. Higher health hybird snipers can rely more on positioning to move up. Late picks are very good so either get a thrower or thrower counter for yourself.

out in the open.tips: If you push enemy into their spawn you usually win since there are only two chokepoints for them to use. You can use gadget/super to open the back wall to create another opening, or use a brawler who can walk on water.

pinball dreams.tips: Balance your comp between agro, control, wallbreak. Prepare for last pick throwers. Basic comp has mid brawler, tank, and tank counter. Throwers shift draft away from basic comp.

double swoosh.tips: Have a brawler good at scouting in the middle, with tanker counter on left and tank on right to apply pressure.

hideout.tips: Focus on having strong early picks. Snipers get easily pushed back, try to get a semi-aggressive brawler and wall break for cheese comps.

center stage.tips: Scouting is very good. Be careful about early picking anti-tanks like Chester and Griff as enemy may not pick tanks to feed your hypercharge. Lots of good options but no late pick will guarantee you win.

safe zone.tips: Decent range to hold middle, high damage and long range on left. Don't bother picking a brawler for defending.

pit stop.tips: Complete base race. 1 defender + 2 rush. Angelo not good until high elo

dueling beetles.tips: Very control based. Have some brawler with decent health to pressure the zone. Damage dealers with solid range are also good on the left. Look out for last pick assassins.

split.tips: Two down right, 1 down left. Don't break open right unless thrower, break open left.

new horizons.tips: Usually both teams end up having a wall break to prevent a thrower/tank/wall peak to camp behind them. Rest of the game is snipers battling in middle. Obligatory Kit cheese warning.

canal grande.tips: Water walking is op. Generic snipers are not that good, throwers and last pick takes run draft. Want a brawler that is generically good at cleaning up messes, thrower that won't die to aggro, and a tank or something aggressive. Controlling middle grass is important.

sneaky fields.tips: Get a balanced comp with a tank or two, and a tank counter or brawler in the middle. Even into a tank counter you may want a tank to pressure them out of the grass.

hard rock mine.tips: Abuse Rico if you're below Masters. Make sure your mid has counterplay to agro. You need at least one person to apply pressure with a tank or hybrid of some sort.

gem fort.tips: Get a brawler with a lot of burst damage or health to hold down their lane or middle of map. Go for a balanced comp with tank, control brawler, and tank counter.

kaboom canyon.tips: Get a high damage long range brawler, a pure Heist damage brawler, then a brawler that can perform some okay defense.

hot potato.tips: Base race since control doesn't work anymore. Get a strong antitank to defend and then the other two brawlers should be rushing the safe. Know who are the threats.

parallel plays.tips: Good defender down left side of left. Middle brawler helps pinch right side of left zone and then helps right lane. Right lane needs someone aggressive who can charge a good super or hypercharge to secure zone time.

open business.tips: Brawler in mid should have decent range and help pinch. Antitank is always good to have for zone time or camp behind a wall. Get wall break for late pick throwers. Do not early pick a thrower.

goldarm gulch.tips: Consider trying different lane strategies or being aware of the enemy doing them. Sometimes you can send someone to sneak down right lane, or you triple stack left bush side and work your way horizontally. Lots of walls and people grouping up so use brawlers that benefit/punish those factors.

flaring phoenix.tips: Thrower left, sniper middle, another person middle or far right. Wait for someone to overextend in the middle or for gas to close in for chaos. Look out for brawlers who can passively charge super.

acute angle.tips: Good mid can setup spawn trap

undermine.tips: Win your first interaction in a lane. If you lose, go to your teammate's lane if they won.

penalty kick.tips: Throwers are OP (except for Moe and Kenji). Best throwers are Barley and Larry & Lawrie so use them or ban them. Very easy to get away with random nonsense so make sure you have a good tank counter as well.

snake prarie.tips: Rush in enemy with tanks or have better vision. Group up to be able to get revenge kills (not close enough for one enemy to teamwipe though). Vision gear runs this map.

below zero.tips: Good brawlers will have high mobility or ball control.

cool box.tips: Open map but it's very punishing if you get pushed back from agro. Be wary of high mobility brawlers that can easily score goals (counter then with stun/slow). Hit your shots, keep good positioning, and catch enemies making mistakes.

super center.tips: Tanks better here compared to other Brawl Hockey maps. Lots of good brawlers to go, so identify what tricks a brawler can use to score and adjust to counter or utilize that. Generally, your team composition should have someone good at scoring and someone good at defending.

dry season.tips: Make sure you have some sort of wallbreak, agro, or a thrower. Have a diverse composition to deal with everything.

starr garden.tips: More walls to peak shots compared to other Brawl Hockey maps. Lots of single shot brawlers are good here (off meta spawner counters). Look out for agro strategies by picking an antitank.
